article.description: Illinois State holds off Missouri State 67-63
article.headline: Illinois State holds off Missouri State 67-63
article.linkText: Illinois State holds off Missouri State 67-63
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. -- Daishon Knight scored 17 points to lead Illinois State past Missouri State 67-63 Tuesday night. Illinois State made just 4 of 19 (21.1 percent) from 3-point range but made 26 of a season-high 36 free throw attempts, while forcing 21 Missouri State turnovers. Illinois State (15-12, 8-7 Missouri Valley) improved to 13-1 when leading with 5 minutes to play this season. Austin Ruder's 3 with 4:53 to play gave the Bears a 58-56 lead, but MSU would make only one more field goal -- a 3-pointer by Gavin Thurman with 24 seconds to play. Illinois State's Reggie Lynch tied the game with a layup 16 seconds later and the Redbirds never trailed again, hitting 10 of 13 free throws in the final 2:37 to seal the win. Bobby Hunter scored 14 and Nick Zeisloft added 11 for Illinois State. Jarmar Gulley led Missouri State (17-10, 7-8) with 24 points.
